  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nBSC's geth fork cannot handle the amount of data properly.\r\nDue to the use of leveldb vs. amount of tx per block, log queries are seriously harming performance.\r\nLooking back a couple of 1000 blocks can already bring down powerful machines.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nCompare BSC's geth fork with the vanilla ones, spot the difference and try to re-implement into turbo-geth.\r\nMaybe getting in touch with the BSC dev team could speed things up.\r\n\r\n# Benefit\r\n\r\nImproved awareness about turbo-geth.",
